uch as   Hilger   or   Hillary  .","German: from a short form of   Hildebrand   or any of a variety of other names, male and female, containing ancient Germanic <i>hild</i> ‘battle’ as the first element."],"variants":[{"name":"Hillock","meanings":["English and Scottish: topographic name for someone who lived ‘(by the) small hill’, from Middle English <i>hillok</i>, a diminutive of <i>hille</i> (Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’). See   Hill  ."]},{"name":"Hills","meanings":["English: variant of   Hill   with genitival <i>-s</i> if a relationship name, attested in Matilda <i>Hilles</i>, 1327 (Somerset), where the genitival form may signify widowhood; or with plural <i>-s</i> if habitational, attested in Johanne <i>de Hyles</i>, 1379 (Bickerstaffe, Lancashire), and Ricardo <i>del Hyles</i>, 1379 (Great Eccleston, Lancashire); or, with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>, probably the most common form."]},{"name":"Hiller","meanings":["German: metronymic from <i>Hille</i>, a pet form of the female personal name <i>Hildegund</i> (see   Hilke  ).","German: from a masculine personal beginning with the ancient Germanic element <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’.","German: variant of <b>Hüller</b> (see   Huller  )."]},{"name":"Hil","meanings":["Altered form of English   Hill  .","Dutch (<b>Van den Hil</b>): topographic name from <i>hil, hul</i> ‘hill’, particularly in the sense of a <i>flight hill</i> above sea level in the southwestern Netherlands."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name corrpted from Hannah, q.v. It is also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"],"variants":[{"name":"Nancy","meanings":["Of uncertain origin. From the 18th century it is clearly used as a pet form of   Ann   (  see  Nan  ), but it may originally have been a similar formation deriving from the common medieval given name   Annis  , a vernacular form of   Agnes .  Nowadays it is an independent name, and was especially popular in America in the 1930s, 40s, and 50s."]},{"name":"Nan","meanings":["Originally a pet form of   Ann   (for the initial <i>N-</i>,  compare  Ned  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Anne Hill was born in 1577, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She married Peter Hill about 1600, in Modbury, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1577–":"1577–Surnud","1580–Male":"1580–Surnud","1603–Male":"1603–Surnud","1604–1667":"1604–1667","1577–Female":"1577–Surnud","1667":"1667","1577":"1577","29 MAY 1603":"29. mai 1603","Abt 1600":"umbes 1600","1580":"1580","1604":"1604","1603":"1603","Wells, Somersetshire, England":"Wells, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Modbury,Devon,England":"Modbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Modbury, Devonshire, England":"Modbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1577–":"1577–Kuollut","1580–Male":"1580–Kuollut","1603–Male":"1603–Kuollut","1604–1667":"1604–1667","1577–Female":"1577–Kuollut","1667":"1667","1577":"1577","29 MAY 1603":"29. toukokuuta 1603","Abt 1600":"noin 1600","1580":"1580","1604":"1604","1603":"1603","Wells, Somersetshire, England":"Wells, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Modbury,Devon,England":"Modbury, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Modbury, Devonshire, England":"Modbury, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1577–":"1577–Décédée","1580–Male":"1580–Décédé","1603–Male":"1603–Décédé","1604–1667":"1604–1667","1577–Female":"1577–Décédée","1667":"1667","1577":"1577","29 MAY 1603":"29 mai 1603","Abt 1600":"environ 1600","1580":"1580","1604":"1604","1603":"1603","Wells, Somersetshire, England":"Wells, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Modbury,Devon,England":"Modbury, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Modbury, Devonshire, England":"Modbury, Devon, Angl